  "lastUpdatedOn": "2013-04-06",
  "religion": "Rickman grew up in a Catholic/Methodist household. Now, he calls theatre his religion.",
  "politicalViews": "Rickman is a Labour supporter and (pretty much) married to a Labour politician.",
  "author": "Tom Kershaw",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "parentId": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Alan Rickman was born and raised in London, England."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Rickman had an upbringing of mixed religious heritage. His mother was a Methodist of Welsh descent and his father was an Irish Catholic.",
      "sourceTitle": "Interview: Angel with Horns – The Guardian",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.alan-rickman.com/articles/angel.html"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " Rickman's father died when he was eight years-old,",
      "sourceTitle": "Alan Rickman – Biography",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000614/bio"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " so it's reasonable to assume that Methodism was more influential in his life than Catholicism."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "parentId": 3,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "However, Rickman–who doesn't really like to talk about his personal life",
      "sourceTitle": "Rickman never mixes acting with personal life",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.goerie.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20081215/ENTERTAINMENT0702/312159963/-1/ENTERTAINMENT07"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 3,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " –hasn't gotten into his own, adult spiritual beliefs. Plus, he played God's messenger in the Catholic-inspired comedy, "
    },
    {
      "parentId": 3,
      "type": "emphasis",
      "text": "Dogma"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 3,
      "type": "text",
      "text": ", and didn't seem to bat an eye at the controversy that swirled around it.",
      "sourceTitle": "A Practicing Catholic On The Religious Storm Of 'Dogma.'",
      "sourceUrl": "http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1999-11-07/news/9911070455_1_jason-mewes-and-smith-dogma-catholic-league"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 4
    },
    {
      "parentId": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "As far as I can tell, Rickman has only commented on his \"religion\" by likening his involvement with live theatre to his own, personal spiritual calling.",
      "sourceTitle": "Alan Rickman: Theatre is my religion…",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B-ivjlSuO90"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " I don't have an interpretation for this–perhaps he's an atheist or perhaps it was just a metaphor for him to describe how much he loves theatre.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 5
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Labour by association"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 6
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Rickman is widely cited as a Labour supporter.",
      "sourceTitle": "Alan Rickman – Biography",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000614/bio"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " But passion for politics is something Rickman says has cooled in his life as he's grown older, seemingly because he's tired of rhetoric and politicians talking the talk:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 7
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 8,
      "parentId": 7
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I find myself becoming less and less enamoured of public statement – I'd rather see it in action.",
      "sourceTitle": "Interview: Angel with Horns – The Guardian",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.alan-rickman.com/articles/angel.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "parentId": 9,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "But his girlfriend of nearly 40 years, Rima Horton, is an economist and Labour politician.",
      "sourceTitle": "Rima Horton",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.rbkc.gov.uk/committees/Members/tabid/62/ctl/ViewCMIS_Person/mid/384/id/212/Default.aspx"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 9,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " I imagine it's a very politically-aware relationship."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 10
    },
    {
      "parentId": 10,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Rickman has been known to get annoyed when politics gets in the way of his \"religion.\" When a play he was directing about an activist protesting Israel's involvement in the Gaza Strip was cancelled for political sensitivity issues, Rickman didn't mince words:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 12,
      "parentId": 11
    },
    {
      "parentId": 12,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "This is censorship born out of fear, and the New York Theatre Workshop, the Royal Court, New York audiences – all of us are the losers.",
      "sourceTitle": "Rickman slams 'censorship' of play about US Gaza activist",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2006/feb/28/usa.israel"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 13
    },
    {
      "parentId": 13,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "So, between that and "
    },
    {
      "parentId": 13,
      "type": "emphasis",
      "text": "Dogma"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 13,
      "type": "text",
      "text": ", Rickman isn't afraid to get into controversy, and he exercises his rights. Good on him."
    }
  ],
